properties.name: Lake Hall (LAK)
properties.description:
The Apollo Community has the most centrally located residence halls on campus and is reserved exclusively for first-year students. It is comprised of four two-story buildings with suite-style floor plans, in which four or five residents occupy a two or three bedroom suite. Each suite includes a shared bathroom and an unfurnished living space. Students can use the space in many different ways, and are encouraged to get creative! Students may bring in additional furnishings for their living space including tables, chairs, entertainment stands, small sofas, beanbags, and more. Each of the four residence halls includes a community lounge area, laundry room, and vending machines.

Location: Apollo Community

Phone Number: 407-882-5016

Website: http://www.housing.ucf.edu/choices/apollo

properties.name: Tower I (T1)
properties.description:
The Towers apartments are nestled in one of the most dynamic areas on campus- Knights Plaza. With concerts, athletic events, the All Knight Study, RWC@Knights Plaza and lots of great retail and dining options, this area of campus is the place to be. Something is always going on at your doorstep. Residents of the Towers are also provided with exclusive resident-only discounts at retailers and many other great Knights Plaza perks.

Location: Towers apartments

Phone Number: 407-882-9400

Website: http://www.housing.ucf.edu/choices/towers/

properties.name: Knights Circle (Off Campus)
properties.description:
Live like you mean it at Knights Circle. Take advantage of renovated buildings, updated units, and outstanding amenities. Sprawling over 60 acres the amenity packages offer a state of the art movie theater, free tanning, fitness area, study lounge, three swimming pools, basketball, tennis and volleyball courts, computer labs, social recreational areas and much more.

Location: 12440 Golden Knight Cir, Orlando, FL

Phone Number: 407-380-5807

Website: http://liveatknightscircle.com

properties.name: The Pointe at Central (Off Campus)
properties.description:
With low prices, vast amenities and friendly staff, The Pointe at Central is a great choice for off-campus housing! A worry-free environment allows you to focus on the most important thing - being a college student. You will experience our best of class amenities such as a 24-hour clubhouse complete with a state-of-the-art fitness center, game room, business center, two resort-style pools and a hot tub, basketball and sand volleyball courts and much more! Located on the University of Central Florida shuttle and Lynx bus routes, the commute is easy!

Location: 2635 College Knight Ct, Orlando, FL

Phone Number: 407-384-6800

Website: http://www.thepointeatcentral.com
